# =====================================================================
# MarQueue-wk-one  ·  .gitignore
# Keeps secrets and noise OUT of your GitHub repo.
# (Security check: no secret keys, passwords, or API keys committed.)
# =====================================================================

# Real secrets live ONLY in .env files (never committed) anywhere in the repo.
# .env.example is safe to commit (it has variable NAMES only, no values).
.env
.env.*
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
!.env.example

# Dependencies / build output (if you add a Node backend later)
node_modules/
dist/
build/

# OS / editor junk
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
.idea/
*.log
